import os
import base64
import threading
import tkinter as tk
from tkinter import filedialog, messagebox, ttk
import pandas as pd
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
from google.auth.transport.requests import Request
from google.oauth2.credentials import Credentials
from google_auth_oauthlib.flow import InstalledAppFlow
from googleapiclient.discovery import build
import joblib
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer
from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix, ConfusionMatrixDisplay
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from matplotlib.backends.backend_tkagg import FigureCanvasTkAgg

SCOPES = ['https://www.googleapis.com/auth/gmail.readonly']

vectorizer_cache = None
model_cache = None

selected_training_path = None  # Will hold your uploaded CSV path

def authenticate_gmail():
    creds = None
    if os.path.exists('token.json'):
        creds = Credentials.from_authorized_user_file('token.json', SCOPES)
    if not creds or not creds.valid:
        if creds and creds.expired and creds.refresh_token:
            creds.refresh(Request())
        else:
            flow =
InstalledAppFlow.from_client_secrets_file('credentials.json', SCOPES)
            creds = flow.run_local_server(port=0)
        with open('token.json', 'w') as token:
            token.write(creds.to_json())
    return creds

def decode_body(body_data):
    if not body_data:
        return "[No body found]"
    body_data = body_data.replace("-", "+").replace("_", "/")
    decoded_bytes = base64.b64decode(body_data)
    soup = BeautifulSoup(decoded_bytes, "lxml")
    return soup.get_text()

def fetch_emails():
    creds = authenticate_gmail()
    service = build('gmail', 'v1', credentials=creds)
    result = service.users().messages().list(userId='me',
maxResults=1000).execute()
    messages = result.get('messages', [])
    email_data = []

    for msg in messages:
        msg_detail = service.users().messages().get(userId='me',
id=msg['id']).execute()
        payload = msg_detail.get('payload', {})
        headers = payload.get('headers', [])
        sender = recipient = subject = ""
        for h in headers:
            name = h.get('name', '').lower()
            if name == 'from': sender = h.get('value', '')
            elif name == 'to': recipient = h.get('value', '')
            elif name == 'subject': subject = h.get('value', '')
        body = "[No body found]"
        parts = payload.get('parts', [])
        if parts:
            for part in parts:
                if part.get('mimeType') == 'text/plain':
                    body = decode_body(part.get('body', {}).get('data'))
                    break
        else:
            body = decode_body(payload.get('body', {}).get('data'))
        email_data.append({'sender': sender, 'recipient': recipient,
'subject': subject, 'body': body})

    df = pd.DataFrame(email_data)
    df.to_csv("FetchedEmails.csv", index=False)
    return df

def load_vectorizer_and_model():
    global vectorizer_cache, model_cache
    if vectorizer_cache is None:
        vectorizer_cache = joblib.load("phishing_model_tfidf.pkl")
    if model_cache is None:
        model_cache = joblib.load("phishing_model_model.pkl")
    return vectorizer_cache, model_cache

def draw_confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred):
    for widget in plot_frame.winfo_children():
        widget.destroy()
    cm = confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred)
    disp = ConfusionMatrixDisplay(confusion_matrix=cm)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(5, 4))
    disp.plot(ax=ax)
    canvas = FigureCanvasTkAgg(fig, master=plot_frame)
    canvas.draw()
    canvas.get_tk_widget().pack(fill=tk.BOTH, expand=True)

def predict_emails():
    vectorizer, model = load_vectorizer_and_model()
    df = pd.read_csv("PredictionEmails.csv", encoding="utf-8").fillna("")

    phishing_keywords = ['free', 'winner', 'urgent']
    df['link_count'] = df['body'].apply(lambda x: x.count('http') if
isinstance(x, str) else 0)
    df['suspicious_keyword_count'] = df['body'].apply(
        lambda x: sum(1 for kw in phishing_keywords if isinstance(x, str)
and kw in x.lower())
    )
    df['body_length'] = df['body'].apply(lambda x: len(x) if isinstance(x,
str) else 0)
    df['uses_public_email'] = df['sender'].apply(
        lambda x: 1 if isinstance(x, str) and ('@gmail.com' in x or '@
yahoo.com' in x) else 0
    )
    df['domain_unknown'] = df['sender'].apply(
        lambda x: 1 if isinstance(x, str) and not any(d in x for d in ['
trusted.com', 'safe.org']) else 0
    )

    texts = df['sender'].astype(str) + ' ' + df['subject'].astype(str) + '
' + df['body'].astype(str)
    tfidf_matrix = vectorizer.transform(texts)
    tfidf_df = pd.DataFrame(tfidf_matrix.toarray(),
columns=vectorizer.get_feature_names_out())

    manual_df = df[['link_count', 'suspicious_keyword_count',
'body_length', 'uses_public_email', 'domain_unknown']]
    full_features = pd.concat([manual_df.reset_index(drop=True),
tfidf_df.reset_index(drop=True)], axis=1)

    preds = model.predict(full_features)
    df['Prediction'] = ['Phishing' if p == 1 else 'Not Phishing' for p in
preds]
    df[['sender', 'subject', 'Prediction']].to_csv("PredictedEmails.csv",
index=False)
    show_prediction_table(df)

    if os.path.exists("TrainingEmails.csv"):
        train_df = pd.read_csv("TrainingEmails.csv")
        if 'label' in train_df.columns:
            phishing_keywords = ['free', 'winner', 'urgent']
            train_df['link_count'] = train_df['body'].apply(lambda x:
x.count('http') if isinstance(x, str) else 0)
            train_df['suspicious_keyword_count'] = train_df['body'].apply(
                lambda x: sum(1 for kw in phishing_keywords if
isinstance(x, str) and kw in x.lower())
            )
            train_df['body_length'] = train_df['body'].apply(lambda x:
len(x) if isinstance(x, str) else 0)
            train_df['uses_public_email'] = train_df['sender'].apply(
                lambda x: 1 if isinstance(x, str) and ('@gmail.com' in x or
'@yahoo.com' in x) else 0
            )
            train_df['domain_unknown'] = train_df['sender'].apply(
                lambda x: 1 if isinstance(x, str) and not any(d in x for d
in ['trusted.com', 'safe.org']) else 0
            )
            texts_train = train_df['sender'].astype(str) + ' ' +
train_df['subject'].astype(str) + ' ' + train_df['body'].astype(str)
            tfidf_train = vectorizer.transform(texts_train)
            tfidf_train_df = pd.DataFrame(tfidf_train.toarray(),
columns=vectorizer.get_feature_names_out())
            manual_train_df = train_df[['link_count',
'suspicious_keyword_count', 'body_length', 'uses_public_email',
'domain_unknown']]
            full_train = pd.concat([manual_train_df.reset_index(drop=True),
tfidf_train_df.reset_index(drop=True)], axis=1)

            y_true = train_df['label']
            y_pred = model.predict(full_train)
            root.after(0, lambda: draw_confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred))

def show_prediction_table(df):
    for widget in table_frame.winfo_children():
        widget.destroy()
    cols = ["No", "Sender", "Subject", "Prediction"]
    tree = ttk.Treeview(table_frame, columns=cols, show="headings")
    for c in cols:
        tree.heading(c, text=c)
        width = 50 if c == "No" else 200 if c == "Prediction" else 300
        tree.column(c, width=width, anchor='center' if c in ["No",
"Prediction"] else 'w')
    for i, row in df.iterrows():
        tree.insert('', 'end', values=(i+1, row['sender'], row['subject'],
row['Prediction']))
    vsb = ttk.Scrollbar(table_frame, orient="vertical", command=tree.yview)
    tree.configure(yscrollcommand=vsb.set)
    vsb.pack(side='right', fill='y')
    tree.pack(fill='both', expand=True)

def run_full_pipeline():
    progress_bar.start()
    threading.Thread(target=_run_full_pipeline, daemon=True).start()

def _run_full_pipeline():
    try:
        if selected_training_path:
            df = pd.read_csv(selected_training_path).fillna("")
            print(f"✅ Loaded custom file: {selected_training_path} with
{len(df)} rows")
        else:
            fetch_emails()
            df = pd.read_csv("FetchedEmails.csv").fillna("")
            print(f"✅ Fetched from Gmail: {len(df)} rows")

        phishing_keywords = ["urgent", "free", "click here", "winner",
"prize"]
        df["label"] = df["body"].apply(
            lambda text: 1 if isinstance(text, str) and any(kw in
text.lower() for kw in phishing_keywords) else 0
        )

        df = df.sample(frac=1, random_state=42).reset_index(drop=True)
        split_idx = int(len(df) * 0.7)
        df_train = df.iloc[:split_idx]
        df_test = df.iloc[split_idx:]

        df_train.to_csv("TrainingEmails.csv", index=False)
        df_test.to_csv("PredictionEmails.csv", index=False)

        print(f"✅ Split: {len(df_train)} train, {len(df_test)} test")

        texts_train = df_train['sender'].astype(str) + ' ' +
df_train['subject'].astype(str) + ' ' + df_train['body'].astype(str)
        vectorizer = TfidfVectorizer(max_features=300)
        tfidf_train = vectorizer.fit_transform(texts_train)
        tfidf_train_df = pd.DataFrame(tfidf_train.toarray(),
columns=vectorizer.get_feature_names_out())

        for dataset in [df_train, df_test]:
            dataset['link_count'] = dataset['body'].apply(lambda x:
x.count('http') if isinstance(x, str) else 0)
            dataset['suspicious_keyword_count'] =
dataset['body'].apply(lambda x: sum(1 for kw in phishing_keywords if
isinstance(x, str) and kw in x.lower()))
            dataset['body_length'] = dataset['body'].apply(lambda x: len(x)
if isinstance(x, str) else 0)
            dataset['uses_public_email'] = dataset['sender'].apply(lambda
x: 1 if isinstance(x, str) and ('@gmail.com' in x or '@yahoo.com' in x)
else 0)
            dataset['domain_unknown'] = dataset['sender'].apply(lambda x: 1
if isinstance(x, str) and not any(d in x for d in ['trusted.com', 'safe.org'])
else 0)

        manual_train_df = df_train[['link_count',
'suspicious_keyword_count', 'body_length', 'uses_public_email',
'domain_unknown']]
        X_train = pd.concat([manual_train_df.reset_index(drop=True),
tfidf_train_df.reset_index(drop=True)], axis=1)
        y_train = df_train['label']

        model_type = model_choice.get()
        if model_type == "Logistic":
            model = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000)
        elif model_type == "KNN":
            model = KNeighborsClassifier()
        elif model_type == "RF":
            model = RandomForestClassifier()
        else:
            raise ValueError("Unknown model type selected.")

        model.fit(X_train, y_train)

        joblib.dump(model, "phishing_model_model.pkl")
        joblib.dump(vectorizer, "phishing_model_tfidf.pkl")

        predict_emails()
        root.after(0, lambda: messagebox.showinfo("Pipeline", f"✅ Full
pipeline with {model_type} completed successfully."))

    except Exception as e:
        root.after(0, lambda e=e: messagebox.showerror("Error", str(e)))
    finally:
        root.after(0, progress_bar.stop)

def run_prediction_only():
    progress_bar.start()
    threading.Thread(target=_run_prediction_only, daemon=True).start()

def _run_prediction_only():
    try:
        predict_emails()
    except Exception as e:
        root.after(0, lambda e=e: messagebox.showerror("Error", str(e)))
    finally:
        root.after(0, progress_bar.stop)

def choose_file():
    global selected_training_path, training_label
    filepath = filedialog.askopenfilename(
        filetypes=[("CSV Files", "*.csv")],
        title="Select a CSV file"
    )
    if filepath:
        selected_training_path = filepath
        training_label.config(text=os.path.basename(filepath), fg="black")

def setup_gui():
    global model_choice, training_label, table_frame, plot_frame,
progress_bar
    root.title("Phishing Detection Pipeline")
    root.geometry("1400x800")
    top = tk.Frame(root)
    top.pack(side='top', fill='x')
    tk.Label(top, text="Phishing Detection System", font=("Helvetica", 16,
"bold")).pack(pady=10)
    tk.Label(top, text="Select Model Type:", font=("Helvetica", 10)).pack()
    model_choice = ttk.Combobox(top, values=["Logistic", "RF", "KNN"])
    model_choice.set("Logistic")
    model_choice.pack()
    tk.Label(top, text="Optional: Upload Custom Training CSV",
font=("Helvetica", 10)).pack(pady=(15, 0))
    tk.Button(top, text="Choose File", command=choose_file).pack()
    training_label = tk.Label(top, text="No custom file loaded", fg="gray")
    training_label.pack()
    tk.Button(top, text="Run Full Pipeline (Train + Predict)",
command=run_full_pipeline, bg="#d17edd", width=40).pack(pady=(20, 5))
    tk.Button(top, text="Run Prediction Only (Skip Training)",
command=run_prediction_only, bg="#cfe2ff", width=40).pack()
    progress_bar = ttk.Progressbar(top, mode="indeterminate")
    progress_bar.pack(pady=(10, 0), fill='x')
    middle = tk.Frame(root)
    middle.pack(side='top', fill='both', expand=True)
    plot_frame = tk.Frame(middle, width=600)
    plot_frame.pack(side='left', fill='both', expand=True)
    table_frame = tk.Frame(middle)
    table_frame.pack(side='left', fill='both', expand=True)
    root.mainloop()

if __name__ == "__main__":
    root = tk.Tk()
    setup_gui()

Cruise with airfare on us!
Book an eligible Norwegian sailing through Southwest® Cruises and we’ll cover the airfare for your second guest from select departure cities.*









Learn more









*Offer available from 6/17/25-7/17/25. Taxes and fees may apply. Subject to additional terms and restrictions. Ask your agent for details.

      $49 Sale Terms and Conditions:
    


        21-day advance purchase required. Purchase from July 1 through July 3, 2025 11:59 p.m. Pacific Time (“Booking Period”). Continental U.S. travel valid August 4 through December 17, 2025. Continental U.S. travel to/from Hawaii, international, and San Juan, Puerto Rico valid August 17 through December 10, 2025. Interisland Hawaii travel valid July 22 through October 1, 2025. Continental U.S. travel blacked out September 1, October 13, November 24 through November 26, and December 1, 2025. Continental U.S. travel to Hawaii, international, and San Juan, Puerto Rico blacked out August 28 through September 2 and November 20 through November 24, 2025. Continental U.S. travel from Hawaii, international, and San Juan, Puerto Rico blacked out August 28 through September 2 and November 28 through December 2, 2025. Interisland Hawaii travel blacked out September 2, 2025. Continental U.S. travel is valid on Mondays, Tuesdays, Wednesdays, and Thursdays. Travel from continental U.S. to Hawaii and international is valid Sundays, Mondays, Tuesdays, and Wednesdays. Travel to continental U.S. from Hawaii and international is valid Tuesdays, Wednesdays, Thursdays, and Fridays. Interisland Hawaii travel is valid Tuesdays and Wednesdays. Travel to/from San Juan, Puerto Rico is valid Mondays, Tuesdays, Wednesdays, and Thursdays. Fares valid on nonstop service where indicated; if not indicated, fares are valid on single connecting service. Displayed prices include all U.S. and international government taxes and fees. Points bookings do not include taxes, fees, and other government/airport charges of at least $5.60 per one-way flight. Seats, days, and markets are limited. Fares may vary by destination, flight, and day of the week and won't be available on some flights that operate during very busy travel times and holiday periods. Travel is available for one-way Basic fares unless otherwise specified. Interisland Hawaii and Cuba travel is available for one-way Wanna Get Away Plus® fares. Fares may be combined with other Southwest Airlines® combinable fares. If combining with other fares, the most restrictive fare's rules apply. Advertised fares may be available on other days of the week, but that's not guaranteed. Basic fares are nonrefundable and non-changeable except as allowed by our 24-hour cancellation policy. Customers may be eligible for a flight credit if their flight is canceled at least 10 minutes prior to the flight's original scheduled departure time. Failure to cancel prior to departure will result in forfeiture of remaining funds on the reservation. Any change in itinerary may result in an increase in fare. Standby travel may require a fare upgrade depending on fare purchased and Rapid Rewards® tier status. Fares are subject to change until ticketed. Offer applies only to published, scheduled service. Additional fees and charges for optional products and services may apply.
      
    





      Southwest Cruises Norwegian BOGO Terms:
    


        Book with Southwest Cruises to receive free airfare for your 2nd guest on select Norwegian Cruise Line sailings. "Buy One, Get One: Airfare" offer applies to economy, round trip flights from select departure gateways only. Offer is valid only for new, individual bookings made between 12:01 a.m. ET on 6/17/25 and 11:59 p.m. ET on 7/17/25 aboard select Norwegian Cruise Line sailings; not all sailing dates may qualify. Guest 1 purchases a full promotional airfare and guest 2 on the same reservation flies free from specific air gateway cities for select 2025 - 2026 sailings Norwegian Cruise Line sailings. Offer is capacity controlled, must be made more than 110 days prior to sailing, not valid for 3rd – 8th guests traveling in the same stateroom. Reservations must be booked more than 110 days prior to sailing to qualify for this promotion. Must call (800) 211-2933 to book BOGO airfare promotion. Not valid for all fares and promotions displaying online and is restricted to certain fare codes. Not valid for categories IX, OX, BX, or MX. Offer and combinability with other promotional offers is subject to change at any time per Norwegian Cruise Line's discretion. Additional restrictions may apply; ask your agent for details. Hurry offer ends 7/17/25!
      







      The account information in this email is only an estimate for a specific point in time. Please reference your Rapid Rewards® account on Southwest.com® for the most up-to-date information on available points, tier status, including tier qualifying points or flights, and Companion Pass® qualifying points or flights.
    

All Rapid Rewards rules and regulations apply.

I’m not talking about small things like salt or matches o! No, I mean literally everything.   And before you think I’m broke-shaming, let me clear the air. This my neighbour is NOT broke. He is farrrr from broke. He’s just an Alaroro. He borrows anything and everything from seasoning cubes to my generator! And I’m not even joking.   The other day, he came to borrow my phone. For what? An interview! Yes o!  You read that right! What happened to his own phone? It fell into a bucket of water sometime last week. At least that's what he told me and ever since, I've not had peace of mind. If he's not borrowing my phone for interviews, he's using it to call his babe. Torrh, justice for the singles.  But today? Today is a great day.  Why? Because as I was scrolling on Jumia this morning, I saw that they were doing a Phone Sale with up to 40% OFF on all phones! If you see the way I ran to my neighbours apartment to give him the gist! There were so many options! From Xiaomi, to Tecno, Infinix, Samsung, and even iPhones!  After a lot of back and forth, he finally settled on a very affordable yet powerful smartphone. And just like that, the countdown to when my phone will be mine again has begun.  Of course you didn’t expect that I would order just his phone. I noticed Jumia also has a sale on home essentials like wall art, beddings, lamps, etc, so I added this Foldable Eye Care Desk Lamp before I checked out. Because, who no like beta thing?  Anyway, that’s all the gist and deals I have for you today. You’re welcome 😌. And remember, we don’t gatekeep around here so, share this with your friends and family. Till next time.  Love,  Jemima from Jumia.Shop Hot Phone Deals Now 🔥Redmi A5 6.88" 3GB RAM/64...₦98,632₦95,632Shop NowThe New ATOUCH Busin...₦94,799₦76,893Shop Now50000 MAh Power Banks Wit...₦27,059₦27,059Shop Now2165 Wireless FM, Torch, ...₦18,000₦10,990Shop Now20000mAh Power Charging B...₦14,174₦7,343Shop NowTiLECC Wireless Lavalier ...₦13,231₦6,999Shop NowIf you'd like to unsubscribe and stop receiving these emails click here

subject: Still need to finish your taxes, Adeoluwa? We've got you covered.
body:
Still need to wrap up your taxes, Adeoluwa? The process is easier than you might think with Credit Karma and TurboTax.

It's as easy as 1-2-3:

1. Just snap a pic of your W-2 and upload it to the Credit Karma app.

2. Finish up on any device when you're ready. We'll prefill key info from your member profile to give you a head start.1

3. TurboTax will guide you through the rest. You can even tap a TurboTax Live expert to take the work (and worries) off your plate.

And that's it! Before you know it, you'll be back to the important stuff - like what's for dinner.

Let's go: https://www.creditkarma.com/u/turbotax-offer

More ways to save with Uber One













More ways to save with Uber One















 






















































 







Earn 10% Uber One credits on car rentals










Members already earn Uber One credits on eligible rides, but what about when you need to rent a car?

Now, you'll earn 10% back in Uber One credits (up to $250) every time you rent a car through Uber.

Whether you're heading out of town or just need a car for the day, car rentals just got more rewarding.












Find a car  









 




















































 








Why rent with Uber?




























 








































Get the right ride for you and your budget






Instantly compare a number of options and prices, and choose from a range of add-ons if you need something extra.
















 


















 























Need a car fast? We’ll bring it






Choose car delivery and have your rental brought straight to you in as little as 2 hours*.








































 


















 








































Turo's now rolling with Uber Rent






From daily drivers to dream cars, you can now discover and book vehicles on Turo directly through the Uber app.
















 
































Rent a car  




















 







 







 

















Offer valid for Uber Rent bookings by Uber One members that are reserved before December 31, 2026 and vehicle pickup is completed before December 31, 2026, while supplies last. Offer redeemable only by Uber One members who receive this offer directly from Uber. Uber Rent Terms and Conditions apply. For qualifying transactions, 10% of the value of your Uber Rent reservation, up to $250, not including applicable taxes, will be applied to your account in Uber One credits upon completion, which may take up to 90 days after the rental pickup date. Uber One credits are earned after completion of eligible rentals and cannot be used in countries outside of the country where the vehicle was booked from. Uber One credits expire after 60 days from the day the Uber One credits are provided and cannot be sold, transferred, exchanged or converted to cash. View Uber One credits in the wallet section of your App. Offer is valid while supplies last and is subject to change without notice. Uber One Membership terms also apply.

*Not available in all locations. Delivery times may be limited based on rental lot operating hours. Check the Uber app for availability.

Every Tuesday members save 30% on fresh groceries like produce, meats, and dairy—all with $0 Delivery Fee! Fresh Tuesdays savings are here today and gone tomorrow, so order before it’s too late.






Order groceries  

 





















































































We know the finer points of fresh









Getting you the freshest groceries starts with our experts in the aisles. Shoppers are trained to get you the crispest greens, freshest fruits, and peak seasonal produce.







Order groceries❯



































 






























Promo expires on 7/1/2025. Promo valid for 30% off. Before taxes and fees, from select stores in the Grocery section of the Uber Eats app. Discount available on your next order only. Eligible orders placed ahead of time must be scheduled for delivery before expiration date. Valid only for those who received it directly from Uber. Taxes and fees still apply. Terms are subject to change. Pickup orders excluded. Other exclusions may apply (e.g., alcohol orders). See the Uber Eats app for details.

The merchant storefront lists the required order minimum for benefits to apply, and may change from time to time. Taxes and additional fees which may apply to your order do not count towards the order minimums. Discounts associated with your membership will apply as a reduction in fees. Uber One credits are earned after completion of eligible rides, and only redeemable on eligible eats and rides orders .

Uber One is a subscription that auto-renews. Your payment method will be charged according to the amount and frequency associated with your chosen membership at sign-up and upon the conclusion of any applicable free trial or promotional period. You can cancel your membership at any time in the Uber One section of the Uber app by selecting Manage Membership, then End Membership. If you cancel less than 24 hours before your next renewal day, you may see a charge that will be automatically refunded. Uber Cash or Uber One credits earned in connection with membership are revocable upon termination of membership. Except where prohibited by law, your subscription charge is non-refundable once your billing cycle begins. Use of Uber One is governed by the terms.

Benefits available only where Uber operates for eligible stores and rides marked with the Uber One icon. Other fees & taxes apply, but do not count towards order minimums or Uber One credits benefits. Receive $0 Delivery Fee on standard delivery, and discounted Service Fee, from participating stores when you meet the order minimums shown on the storefront.  6% Uber One credits earned after completion of eligible rides and expire 60 days after being added to your wallet. Subject to change. View the Renewable Membership T&Cs.

subject: Protect Yourself: How to Spot Email Scams Fast
body:
Adeoluwa Afolabi 
                                     
                                     - 
                                    How to tell if an email is really from PayPal
                                  
                                
                              
                            
                          
                          
                            
                              
                                
                                  
                                    View Online
                                  
                                
                              
                            
                          
                        
                      
                    
                  
                
              
            
            
          
        
      
    
    
    
    
  



How to spot emailscams quicklyHi Adeoluwa,As digital scams are getting more sophisticated, it’s important to learn how to spot common signs of fraud and report it to help stay safe online.If you receive a communication – a call, text, or email – that you think may not really be from PayPal, don’t respond, share any personal information, click on any links or open any attachments. Simply forward it to Phishing@paypal.com and delete it.Learn More

Here are some simple tips to stay safe from scams and phishing:

1.
Be cautious if the email:
                                                                  Doesn't use your full name and has a generic greeting
                                                                
                                                                  Has incorrect logos, design or looks strange
                                                                
                                                                  Contains suspicious website links
                                                                
                                                                  Includes attachments and software.
                                                                

2.
Be wary of false urgency.Scams often create a false sense of urgency. If in doubt, log in to your PayPal account to check for urgent messages or notifications.
3.
Watch out for offers that seems too good to be true.Scammers may use false promises like money in exchange for a favor, lottery wins, or unsolicited job offers.

4.
Never provide personal, credit card or account information via email, text or phone.Always log in at PayPal.com to update your personal information, including your full name, credit and debit card numbers, bank account numbers, your driver's license number, email, and password.
Find out more

      $49 Sale Terms and Conditions:
    


        21-day advance purchase required. Purchase from July 1 through July 3, 2025 11:59 p.m. Pacific Time (“Booking Period”). Continental U.S. travel valid August 4 through December 17, 2025. Continental U.S. travel to/from Hawaii, international, and San Juan, Puerto Rico valid August 17 through December 10, 2025. Interisland Hawaii travel valid July 22 through October 1, 2025. Continental U.S. travel blacked out September 1, October 13, November 24 through November 26, and December 1, 2025. Continental U.S. travel to Hawaii, international, and San Juan, Puerto Rico blacked out August 28 through September 2 and November 20 through November 24, 2025. Continental U.S. travel from Hawaii, international, and San Juan, Puerto Rico blacked out August 28 through September 2 and November 28 through December 2, 2025. Interisland Hawaii travel blacked out September 2, 2025. Continental U.S. travel is valid on Mondays, Tuesdays, Wednesdays, and Thursdays. Travel from continental U.S. to Hawaii and international is valid Sundays, Mondays, Tuesdays, and Wednesdays. Travel to continental U.S. from Hawaii and international is valid Tuesdays, Wednesdays, Thursdays, and Fridays. Interisland Hawaii travel is valid Tuesdays and Wednesdays. Travel to/from San Juan, Puerto Rico is valid Mondays, Tuesdays, Wednesdays, and Thursdays. Fares valid on nonstop service where indicated; if not indicated, fares are valid on single connecting service. Displayed prices include all U.S. and international government taxes and fees. Points bookings do not include taxes, fees, and other government/airport charges of at least $5.60 per one-way flight. Seats, days, and markets are limited. Fares may vary by destination, flight, and day of the week and won't be available on some flights that operate during very busy travel times and holiday periods. Travel is available for one-way Basic fares unless otherwise specified. Interisland Hawaii and Cuba travel is available for one-way Wanna Get Away Plus® fares. Fares may be combined with other Southwest Airlines® combinable fares. If combining with other fares, the most restrictive fare's rules apply. Advertised fares may be available on other days of the week, but that's not guaranteed. Basic fares are nonrefundable and non-changeable except as allowed by our 24-hour cancellation policy. Customers may be eligible for a flight credit if their flight is canceled at least 10 minutes prior to the flight's original scheduled departure time. Failure to cancel prior to departure will result in forfeiture of remaining funds on the reservation. Any change in itinerary may result in an increase in fare. Standby travel may require a fare upgrade depending on fare purchased and Rapid Rewards® tier status. Fares are subject to change until ticketed. Offer applies only to published, scheduled service. Additional fees and charges for optional products and services may apply.
      
    





      Southwest Cruises Norwegian BOGO Terms:
    


        Book with Southwest Cruises to receive free airfare for your 2nd guest on select Norwegian Cruise Line sailings. "Buy One, Get One: Airfare" offer applies to economy, round trip flights from select departure gateways only. Offer is valid only for new, individual bookings made between 12:01 a.m. ET on 6/17/25 and 11:59 p.m. ET on 7/17/25 aboard select Norwegian Cruise Line sailings; not all sailing dates may qualify. Guest 1 purchases a full promotional airfare and guest 2 on the same reservation flies free from specific air gateway cities for select 2025 - 2026 sailings Norwegian Cruise Line sailings. Offer is capacity controlled, must be made more than 110 days prior to sailing, not valid for 3rd – 8th guests traveling in the same stateroom. Reservations must be booked more than 110 days prior to sailing to qualify for this promotion. Must call (800) 211-2933 to book BOGO airfare promotion. *************************************
The Mid-Year Challenge Starts Today 🏅
*************************************

Trying to be more consistent with your Bible habit?

Take on the Mid-Year Challenge! 
( https://www.bible.com/reading-plans?utm_medium=email&utm_source=Email&utm_campaign=2025-07-mid-year-challenge-starts&utm_content=inline&lid=nm3qhqjefc1o )


Regularly spending time in God’s Word often requires
perseverance and endurance. By taking on the Mid-Year Challenge,
you can focus on both skills while building your Bible habit.

Just complete one day of any Plan for seven consecutive days
this month to earn a special Badge!

2025 Mid-Year Challenge Badge Choose a Plan and take on the
Mid-Year Challenge today!

subject: TIP 102 Week 5: Halfway There! Study Groups & Mock Interviews 🚀
body:
Greetings, Terrific TIP Engineers!

We hope you had a fantastic Week 4 and are balancing food, friends, and
free time as we hit the midpoint of your program journey—Week 5! 🎉

Group Mates, in awe,

as we approach the halfway point of our course!
What’s Ahead in Week 5?

📌 TIP Lectures & Main Topics

   -

    For both TIP 102:
   -

       ✅ Session 1: Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) & Linked Lists
      -

       ✅ Session 2: Mock Interviews!

📌 Unit Work Continues—Stay on track with your current unit(s)!

=========
🚀 New TIP Features: Study Groups!

Study Groups
Want to collaborate, problem-solve, and reinforce concepts with your peers?
Start or join a study group! Registration for these will start this week! Need
a reminder of what these are?:

   - Watch the 2 m intro
   
   by Mx. Z!
      -

      Study Group Overview
      
      -

      Sign up
      
      to Lead or Join a Study Group!

TIP Feature Persisting - Buddy Breakout Group Creation!

We’re continuing with Buddy Breakout Groups for Weeks 5 and beyond! This is
an optional feature which allows you to work with the same group of
students week after week!

   -

   To have a Buddy Breakout Group for next class, you will need to Sign up
   
   by 9:00 AM Pacific Time the day of your class session.
   -

      ALL members must fill out an instance of the form, selecting each
      other to be matched.
      -

      Please watch this Overview Loom
      
      by Mx. Z if you’ve forgotten the steps!
      -

      If your Buddy Breakout Group has already been approved you do not
      need to sign up again!
      -

         If you would like to change your group, please email
         support@codepath.org

=========


We’re Halfway There!

Week 5 is the midpoint of your TIP journey, and we’re so, so glad you’re
here. Keep up the great work, and let’s make the second half even stronger!
💪🚀

Warmly,
Maxwell & The TIP Adaptive Team

=========

📢 Need help? Post in your section’s Slack Help channel or email
support@codepath.org

⚠️ Please DO NOT reply to this email—all replies will be routed to
support@codepath.org.


--

subject: Reminder: Upcoming Bank Holiday
body:
Deposits may be delayed by one business day
Reminder: Friday, July 4 is a bank holiday     We want to give a
friendly reminder that Friday, July 4 is a federal bank holiday.
This means that all deposits, including direct deposits, may be
delayed by up to one business day.

Here's a sneak peek of other upcoming bank holidays: * Monday,
September 1
* Monday, October 13

If you need to move money into your Current Account, remember
that you can instantly fund using a debit card. Debit card
funding is not impacted by bank holidays.

Adeoluwa,

Today is the last day of June, which means this is your LAST CHANCE to apply for this month’s $2,000 scholarship!1 (https://www.sallie.com/e3t/Ctc/OU+113/d5v0pL04/VXkw7F9ghQNYW8Py_dQ706brLW4qM5Xr5yqRjRN4qMxLn3prCCW7Y8-PT6lZ3lGW4xrXK_66MFspVV-QPB17GTCVVwxjC572lYnwVNCWzf38NJ18W5V9Q1N2cxxMSN5WM-YZfbmbtW2sW7618GXJrgW18G0jZ5sY48MW6nbJl86Lqg8fVTSMx75lTmv5VCTtrp215Ms0VfPsSb4S_tsgW3Tp3Yl4V6xlbW1HWT9-1StxPSW5sqdGK2lKwsQW8hHMdW1vZnSnW4XvsH54TPqMtW1Jm5Xl9334GBW13KCRj6j0tZqW4ZRPBR8R6Zp8W7QQd4T1X3GxNW91dfPT2ZNh-6VCWF-z2NN1QRW4Rtmrs4JGw0rW1YK8p833BKMSN29HhpfHxcqwf6rdv-j04 )

We encourage students and families to start with savings, grants, scholarships, and federal student loans to pay for college. Evaluate all anticipated monthly loan payments, and how much the student expects to earn in the future, before considering a private student loan.

Tickets to EES 2025, 1:1 Coaching, Resume Review Week

Hi Adeoluwa ,

Congratulations! By completing Week 4 in your CodePath course, you're now eligible to take part in two of our most popular services: Resume Review Week and 1:1 Professional Career Coaching.

>>>> EES 2025

Plus, don't forget to reserve your spot for the Emerging Engineers Summit in September!

Over 4,000 tickets have already been claimed, and we expect to sell out before the event. EES is exclusively for course completers, but you can apply now and we'll hold your spot until you complete your course! (https://cDXtc04.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/T+113/cDXtc04/VVx4Gj1NxDZsMTBZqjpM9g9W2XSKgS5ypg0YMDyKnK3pyd0W95jsWP6lZ3lXW3cbWQq3Q82jRW1TfzVj35rzl0W1Wl5mh7b_8p3W8kmfVW24GL5jW6LDhsK5S9kmNN7r2jsBSzvXMW8Kxl0B5t3KNNW4QR2Pl7Q42T1N2W-nHD4Xg0-W5MG07s534Z2DW28dHpW7kVrKrW8XCtPR74_bMNW18tZYJ4PQGpFW3NGynp6GBWRpW2vLPrz67TTVzW2Zsp9V4qXDdZW1FqYQn6Z-lH2VVgL0J1KflDXW1_nm6f6JyqSqW7vyl5y2LRvHYN5RWLq0h5P1DW71B_WK1ZGBhJW4WLyqK3k5JZzN74NZkKgff8zW8xwLvV82zbB1W3lCPNb4MmZyMW6bq3jn3CqcPVW6R9YG451LxNfW2PGDjP7Zw4_6W7l-dwP4BpNF_f5r-hg004 )

📝 Resume Review Week

Get personalized resume feedback and career advice from tech professionals working at companies like Capital One, Microsoft and many more. Upload a resume, and choose a time to meet via Zoom for a 30 minute 1:1 session.

This semester's Resume Review Week will run from August 11th - 14th. Registration will open on July 15th, and we expect popular timeslots to go fast!

Next Step: Watch out for the email on July 15th to claim your spot!

📣 1:1 Professional Career Coaching

Our professional coaches bring decades of experience in career support and tech recruiting. They are here to support you! Book a one-on-one meeting to discuss:

- Job search strategy, guidance and support
- Behavioral interview advice
- Elevator pitch advice or practice
- Networking guidance and trouble-shooting
- Or anything related to your career!

body:
TIP102: Unit 4 Version A (Standard)  - Summer 2025 - Submission Confirmation


Congratulations on completing this week's assignment, **TIP102: Unit 4 Version A (Standard)  - Summer 2025**. Here are some key details to keep in mind:

- **My Report Tab Update:** You can expect an update in your My Report tab on the course portal within 6-12 hours after submitting your assignment. _The My Report Tab is only accessible by admitted students. _
- **Technical Support:** If you have any technical questions, attend the optional office hours or post in the help channel. Tag your TSRs (Technical Support Representatives) outside class hours or your TFs (Tech Fellows) during class sessions.
- **Submission Requirement:** Remember to submit each assignment by the deadline or within the 48-hour deadline extension. Missing one submission may change your course participation to observer status.
- **Contact for Concerns:** Reach out to [support@codepath.org](mailto:support@codepath.org) for specific concerns.

Keep up the great work on your TIP102: Unit 4 Version A (Standard)  - Summer 2025!

 

Thanks,  
**CodePath Team**

any hiring challenges or conduct interviews for any company. Please directly contact the company
that sent you the invite for such purposes.

subject: AI, Internships & Career Glow-Ups — IBM’s Got You Covered, ADEOLUWA
body:
IBM Entry Level Careers 

  	[1]  

   	Unlock your Career 

	Hi ADEOLUWA,

 Welcome to the June 2025 edit of your Early Career Kick Start newsletter! 

	In this edition we’re highlighting, a Product Manager Intern's journey and her insights into the unique value of IBM internships, IBM CEO Arvind Krishna's vision for the future, spotlighting the transformative power of AI, automation, and hybrid cloud, IBM apprentices reinventing their careers through the Apprenticeship Program, and free on-the-go learning and resources to power up your AI skills. 

	Enjoy the read! 

   	Fresh Perspective 

   	Immerse yourself in Austeja's journey as an IBM Product Manager Intern. Discover how this experience has not only molded her professional path but also unlocked a universe of innovation. Explore what sets IBM internships apart and gain insights into a day in the life of a tech professional. 

   	[2] Read the blog 

   	Around the World 

   	At Think 2025, IBM CEO Arvind Krishna revealed IBM's vision for the future, emphasizing the transformative power of AI, automation, and hybrid cloud in driving business growth and innovation. Dive into this and many other keynotes to understand what technologies can propel your career forward. 

   	[3] Watch the Keynote 

   	Spotlight Story 

   	Say hello to IBM’s apprentices, who are reinventing their careers through the Apprenticeship Program. Listen to their inspiring stories, from pushing personal limits to making career pivots, as they advise aspiring candidates. Don't wait to take a leap into your future — apply for the IBM Apprenticeship Program today! 

   	[4] Read the story 

   	Your Free Monthly Brain Booster 

   Every month we’re highlighting one piece of learning to support you in growing your skills.

	This month’s knowledge boost: On-the-go AI learning, offering free courses from experts at IBM.   

	"Why should I care about this?" 

	Embark on your AI journey through flexible, self-paced lessons suitable for all skill levels. Expand your understanding with beginner-friendly courses that cover essential AI concepts, generative AI, and ethics, while also engaging with practical lessons on prompt writing, resume improvement, and industry applications such as sports tech, machine learning, deep learning, natural language processing, and computer vision. Begin your learning today; no coding skills are needed. 

   	[5] Start learning 

   	Keep Your Profile Updated 

   	To make sure we’re sending this email to the correct audience, please ensure your profile is up to date in our database by filling out the [6] Talent Network Form using the email you signed up with. The new fields you enter will replace your previous profile. 

	Keep in touch!

	As always, if you need any assistance, drop us a message via social media in the links below. 

	The IBM Talent Acquisition Team

subject: Have you tried our free videos + practice questions?
body:
Khan has thousands of free videos, articles, and exercises! 



 Hi, 
Congrats on your first month with Khan Academy! Have you had a chance to try out our free videos, articles, and practice questions?

If not, I highly recommend just starting with a quick search for whatever you’re teaching next:

 Search now  You’ll find high-quality resources that you can share with your students immediately. And since Khan is a nonprofit, they’re all 100% free - no ads, no subscriptions.

Enjoy!
-Aviv

PS: Have a question? We’re here to help — contact our Community Support Team  for a rapid response or post in our Teach with Khan community  to learn from your fellow educators.

Better learning.Better results.
The way we learn is just as important as what we’re learning. To get more out of your efforts and your time, ask yourself these questions. 


           1
What have I learned before? 
Think about your past projects and experiences. Focus on what went well, what motivated you along the way, and how this can help you now.                      2
What did I learn today? 
Even when we’re not taking a course, we still learn through everyday activities and interactions. Reflect on your day and anything you’d want to improve.                      3
What should I learn next? 
Based on your takeaways from the last two questions, decide which skills you should learn now to reach the next step in your journey.




Remember, progress makes perfect. Even just a little bit of learning each day will help you get closer to where you want to be.

         Members, get 50% off grocery orders  on $40+ order this July 4th


      







The weather’s heating up, and so is the grill. Save up to $30  on burgers, watermelon, and more delivered straight to you this July 4th weekend. Plus, members get $0 delivery fees on eligible orders.






Order groceries  

 


























































 






































40% off goods for your grill









No need to pause the festivities. Cook up some fun and save on steaks, sausages, burgers, and more! *







Shop BBQ essentials❯




































 






































Your BBQ sidekick: 40% off salty snacks









From party mixes to chips and popcorn, get your salty snack table covered for the Fourth. *







Shop party snacks❯




































 






































Stock up on refreshing sips









The cooler’s calling. Save on 2-liter bottles of Coca-cola, Sprite, orange juice, and more.







Shop party sips❯




































 






































Stars, stripes, and SPF: 40% off sunscreen









Stock up on SPF and stay sun-safe with savings on sunscreen essentials. *







Shop sunscreen❯























































Promo expires on Jul 1, 2025 12:30AM local time. Promo valid for 50% off on orders of $40 or more up to max $30. Before taxes, fees and promotions, from select stores in the Grocery section of the Uber Eats app. Eligible orders placed ahead of time must be scheduled for delivery before expiration date. Valid only for those who received it directly from Uber. Taxes and fees still apply. Terms are subject to change. Pickup orders excluded. Other exclusions may apply (e.g., alcohol orders). See the Uber Eats app for details.

Benefits available only for eligible stores marked with the Uber One icon. Other fees & taxes apply, but do not count towards order minimums. Participating restaurants and non-grocery stores: $15 minimum order to receive $0 Delivery Fee. Participating grocery stores: $35 minimum order to receive $0 Delivery Fee. Membership savings applied as a reduction to service fees. Subject to change.

View the Renewable Membership T&Cs.

*Promos expire on 07/06/2025 at 11:59 PM EST. Discount on select items and merchants across Grocery & Retail, see app for details. Minimum basket and maximum savings apply, some restrictions apply, see app for details. While supplies last.

subject: Competition Launch: NeurIPS - Ariel Data Challenge 2025
body:
Kaggle








Hi Adeolu Afolabi,

Can ML models help uncover signs of life on distant worlds? That's what  
we're exploring in the NeurIPS - Ariel Data Challenge 2025.

In this competition, you'll work with simulated telescope data from the  
European Space Agency's upcoming Ariel mission to recover faint chemical  
signals from exoplanet atmospheres. These signals are incredibly subtle and  
often obscured by complex, time-dependent noise—making this a uniquely  
challenging opportunity for the Kaggle community.

You'll build models that clean up messy telescope data to detect the  
spectral fingerprints of alien atmospheres. The dataset includes realistic  
star–planet systems, stellar limb darkening effects, and a wide range of  
atmospheric profiles, helping scientists improve the accuracy of their  
analyses.





Total Prizes:

$50,000


Entry Deadline:

September 17, 2025




Learn More



Your work could help accelerate exoplanet research and contribute to  
answering one of astronomy's most profound questions: Are we alone in the  
universe?

Good luck,

Sohier Dane
Kaggle Data Scientist



Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043

This email was sent to adeoluafolabi7@gmail.com because you indicated that  
you'd like to receive news and updates about Kaggle. If you don't want to  
receive these emails in the future, please unsubscribe here. You can also  
change your preferences on your account's profile page by logging in at  
kaggle.com.

 Promotional Companion Pass® Terms and Conditions: 
  Register for this promotion, then book one qualifying round trip or two qualifying one-way Southwest® flights between 8:00 a.m. Central Time (“CT”) on June 24, 2025 and 11:59 p.m. CT on June 27, 2025 (the “Promotion Period”) for travel from June 24, 2025 to August 31, 2025 (the "Travel Period"), and fly during the Travel Period to earn a promotional Companion Pass® valid for use between September 8, 2025 and November 15, 2025. Basic fares are not qualifying flights for this promotion. 
  To register for this promotion, you will need to provide your Southwest Rapid Rewards® account number at the time of registration. If you do not have a Rapid Rewards® account number, you may register for an account by going online to Southwest.com/rapidrewards to become a Member. Rapid Rewards accounts are free. Member must register for this promotion, book one qualifying round trip or two qualifying one-way Southwest flights during the Promotion Period for travel during the Travel Period, and fly during the Travel Period. Registration must be completed prior to booking and commencement of travel. Valid on new qualifying flights booked during the Promotion Period for travel during the Travel Period and flown within the Travel Period. Member’s qualifying flights must be booked through Southwest.com®, the Southwest® Mobile App, swabiz.com (SWABIZ®), Global Distribution System (GDS), or Southwest Partner Services (SPS) distribution channels with Southwest Airlines inventory during the Promotion Period for travel that must be completed during the Travel Period. Member's Rapid Rewards account number must be entered at the time of booking Member's qualifying flight to earn a promotional Companion Pass® valid for use between September 8, 2025 and November 15, 2025. A qualifying one-way flight for this promotion is a one-way flight on Southwest Airlines® from an origin city to a destination city, including any intermediate stops and/or connections on Southwest Airlines. A qualifying round trip flight for this promotion is a round trip flight on Southwest Airlines from an origin city to a destination city and back to the originating airport or carrier-recognized co-terminal. Valid on new reservations booked within the Promotion Period for travel during the Travel Period only. Travel booked or flown prior to registration for this promotion is not eligible for this promotional Companion Pass offer. Travel date is determined by the qualifying flight(s) original scheduled departure time. Qualifying flights must be flown by the same Member. Redemption reservations and Cash + Points bookings qualify for this promotional offer. Cash + Points bookings will earn Rapid Rewards points, tier qualifying points for A-List and A-List Preferred status, and Companion Pass qualifying points on the portion of the base fare that is paid with dollars. Companion Pass, charter flights, group travel, Basic fares, and Southwest Vacations® packages do not qualify as one-way or round trip flights for this promotion. Changes made within the Promotion Period are allowed if the qualifying travel is still completed in the Travel Period. Changes made to any itinerary after the Promotion Period may eliminate qualification for this promotion.  
  The promotional Companion Pass is valid from September 8, 2025 through November 15, 2025 and allows you to designate one person to fly with you, free of airline charges (does not include taxes and fees from $5.60 one-way) on flights purchased by you, booked through Southwest, and completed between September 8, 2025 and November 15, 2025. Visit Southwest.com/rrterms for a complete list of Companion Pass rules. No Rapid Rewards points nor tier or Companion Pass qualifying points will be awarded for flights taken by the Companion when flying on a promotional Companion Pass or Companion Pass reservation. Member is limited to one Companion Pass at a time. You may change your designated Companion up to three times while you have promotional Companion Pass. If you earn Companion Pass in 2025 by earning 135,000 Companion Pass qualifying points or flying 100 qualifying flights, any changes to your designated Companion during the time you have a promotional Companion Pass will reduce the number of changes you can make to your designated Companion in the 2025 calendar year. For example, if you earn a promotional Companion Pass through this promotion, change your designated Companion twice during the validity period for promotional Companion Pass, and later in 2025 earn Companion Pass, you would only be able to change your designated Companion one more time in 2025. Companion Pass is nontransferable. All Rapid Rewards rules and regulations apply and can be found at Southwest.com/rrterms. Southwest reserves the right to amend, suspend, or change the Rapid Rewards program and/or Rapid Rewards program rules at any time without notice. Rapid Rewards Members do not acquire property rights in accrued points. The number of points needed for a particular Southwest flight is set by Southwest and will vary depending on destination, time, day of travel, demand, fare type, point redemption rate, and other factors, and is subject to change at any time until the booking is confirmed.

Please reference your Rapid Rewards® account on Southwest.com® for the most up-to-date information on available points, tier status, including tier qualifying points or flights, and Companion Pass® qualifying points or flights.

Africa is calling -- and Turkish Airlines is ready to take you there with comfort, care, and dependable service.
Round-trip flights from the U.S. to leading African destinations [ https://www.asaptickets.com/pro/turkish-airlines-deals-to-africa?msg=3&mfs=nl_eco_us_africa&line=8669614007&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_source=email&utm_campaign=af-tk-june-27 ] start from just $759* total, but these fares will not stay around for long.
If you're returning to reconnect with family or looking to explore horizons, this is the moment to secure a trip that blends reliability, warmth, and global reach. Turkish Airlines provides long-haul comfort, globally inspired meals, and smooth connections through Istanbul, designed to make each part of your journey feel effortless.
Imagine yourself arriving in Accra, where coastal views meet deep tradition, or touching down in Lagos, a city full of momentum and culture. Nairobi awaits with blue skies and unforgettable landscapes, while Addis Ababa has layers of history and heart. You might find yourself in Johannesburg, a place of both modern energy and powerful heritage, or relaxing on the tranquil shores of Zanzibar.
With flexible scheduling and personalized support [ https://www.asaptickets.com/open-phone-call?phone=8669614007 ] throughout the booking process, Turkish Airlines ensures you arrive at your destination and feel comfortable along the way. subject: 5 popular software engineering certifications
body:
Career Chat

By Coursera


By Coursera

    
    
    Read this article on LinkedIn to join the conversation
Read on LinkedIn
https://www.linkedin.com/comm/pulse/5-popular-software-engineering-certifications-coursera-bkhpe?lipi=urn%3Ali%3Apage%3Aemail_email_series_follow_newsletter_01%3BjYUwPwkFTK%2BCsFAgjygJlQ%3D%3D&midToken=AQEGTZsEbwA4Fg&midSig=3HjsCy9hFNjbQ1&trk=eml-email_series_follow_newsletter_01-null-0-read_more_banner_cta_&trkEmail=eml-email_series_follow_newsletter_01-null-0-read_more_banner_cta_-null-j5vpgy~mce3h6e5~ag-null-null&eid=j5vpgy-mce3h6e5-ag&otpToken=MTMwNDFiZTgxNTJkY2RjM2IzMmUwZmViNDExYmU3YmQ4N2NiZDM0OTlmYTg4NzZjN2JjZjA2Njk0ODUzNTlmM2YwZDNkNWU5NTNlNWMwZTQ2MGExZGY5YjNlYzg4M2MzYzA0MGZhZmQ1Zjk4YjA4NTcwZjAzMjA1LDEsMQ%3D%3D
  
Hiya! There are few things more professionally satisfying than having your skills and expertise recognized by others. When that recognition comes in the form of a certification, it means that your hard-earned skills have been validated by an industry-leading organization.  Much like the machine learning, IT, and data analytics certifications we covered in previous issues, software engineering certifications can help you qualify for higher salaries, new job prospects, and more advancement opportunities. Regardless of where you are on your career journey, there’s likely a certification out there that can help validate your skill set to both current and future employers.  Below, we explore five such certifications that you may consider if you’re a software engineer. There’s plenty to explore, so let’s get started.  But, first: Do you want access to 10,000+ courses, certificates, and programs for 50% off? For a limited time, you can save 50% on an annual Coursera Plus subscription with our early bird summer sale. Access courses in AI, technology, business, and more from industry experts like IBM, Google, and Microsoft.  💻5 popular software engineer certifications If you’re seeking career growth, a software engineer certification may help. Whether you’re just entering the field or already have extensive experience, consider obtaining one of these software engineer certifications:  1. Professional Software Engineering Master Certification (PSEM): The PSEM, offered by the IEEE Computer Society, validates the holder’s knowledge of key areas of software engineering, such as design, testing, and project management. While there are no prerequisites to register for the certification exam, IEEE CS recommends that test takers should have completed at least four years of college in computer science or a related field and have a minimum of four years of relevant work experience.  2. Oracle Database SQL Certified Associate: This Oracle certification demonstrates your knowledge of foundational elements of SQL development and its uses with Oracle databases. There aren’t any requirements to register for the certification exam, but Oracle suggests that qualified candidates have knowledge of general computing concepts and command line interfaces, and experience working in command line.  💡 Get hands-on practice: Check out LearnQuest’s Oracle SQL Databases Specialization to build knowledge of Oracle SQL Databases.  3. CompTIA Security+: The CompTIA Security+ certification is well-suited for software engineers with cybersecurity experience who want to build their skills and demonstrate their proficiency to potential employers. To qualify for the certification exam, you’ll need at least two years of experience in a security or systems administration position and already hold CompTIA Network+ certification.  💡 Get hands-on practice: Packt’s CompTIA Security+ Certification (SY0-701): The Total Course Specialization covers exam topics like risk management, cryptography, and secure networks.  4. Amazon Web Services (AWS) Certified Developer - Associate: Earning an AWS Certified Developer certification demonstrates your proficiency working with AWS cloud-based applications, including developing, testing, and debugging with it. There aren’t any requirements for the certification except to pass the exam, and once you do, you’ll be eligible for more advanced AWS certifications.  💡 Get hands-on practice: Build job-relevant skills in Amazon’s Junior Software Developer Professional Certificate and prepare for the exam through Whizlab’s Exam Prep DVA-C02: AWS Certified Developer Associate Specialization.  5. Certified Secure Software Lifecycle Professional (CSSLP): If you’re a software engineer who wants to demonstrate your proficiency in software security and the software development life cycle (SDLC), consider obtaining CSSLP certification. To be eligible for the certification exam, you’ll need four years of cumulative qualified SDLC professional experience or three years of experience and a four-year college degree in a related field.  💡 Get hands-on practice: Infosec’s Certified Secure Software Lifecycle Professional (CSSLP) course is specifically designed to prepare you for the CSSLP exam.  🖥️ Build your software skills with a Coursera Plus Interested in building the skills you need to advance your software engineering career and prepare for certification? Subscribe to Coursera Plus from now until June 30, 2025, to receive 50% off an annual subscription. Gain access to 10,000+ courses, resume-building certificates, and top programs from Google, Microsoft, and more—including all of the programs suggested above! Okay, that’s it for this week, friends! Before you start prepping for your next certification, let us know what software engineering skills you’re looking to build next in the comment section below. Catch you next week!  Have a career question you’d like us to answer next? Share it below. Still reading this section? Well, hey, thanks for taking the time! Here’s a wildcard course recommendation for you, gakusei.

Replacing legacy technologies is never as simple as buying new solutions. Whether your goal is to modernize apps, improve cyber resilience, or implement Zero Trust security, you need a comprehensive strategy — one that covers everything from technical integration to change management. This month, theNET offers insights for building strategies that can accelerate key technology initiatives and help you achieve business objectives. Modernization is a CxO team sport What's new: 69% of digital transformation projects run behind schedule — and many ultimately fail. Why it matters: To succeed with IT modernization, organizations need more than ambition and resources: They need to align their C-suite on essential responsibilities.  Article (7 min read) Reimagining cyber resilience What’s new: From massive-scale DDoS attacks to AI-powered phishing schemes, organizations face threats that can’t be handled with a collection of legacy point solutions. Why it matters: Addressing today’s threats requires a shift from traditional security and data backup solutions to a more holistic cyber resilience strategy. Article (8 min read) Solving the perimeter problem What’s new: The days of perimeter-based security are over. That legacy model can’t protect a hybrid workforce using cloud-based apps. Why it matters: Tech leaders agree that Zero Trust security is the way forward, but many need a new strategy to progress with their journey. subject: CS#312: The downward spiral most people get stuck in (+ how to reverse it)
body:
View image: (https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/8fe2793f-ceef-44fa-9dd8-211e8d60e2a9/image.png?t=1750970337)
Caption: 

Have you ever wondered why two people can face the same challenge, but respond in completely different ways? In today’s _Mentor's Corner_, I've been pondering this question, and I think I've identified a key factor that often goes overlooked: the power of our ‘beliefs’. Also, if you’re on a job search, read the resume advice in the bottom half of the email.

_Estimated read time_: 6 minutes 35 seconds (_longer than usual but worth it imho_)

———————————————————————————

----------
———————————————————————————


----------## The downward spiral most people get stuck in (+ how to reverse it)

Here’s a question:

What decides whether you “win” at life & in your career or “lose”? (No matter what your definition of “winning” and “losing” is)

Is it money? 

Connections? Knowledge? Wisdom? Willpower? Hard work?

All these obviously help. 

But what if I told you it wasn’t any of these things? 

What if I told you _there's an "X-factor"_ operating behind the scenes that secretly determines who you date, the company you work for, the money you earn, how much crap you take from your boss… and even how "popular" you are in the office?

Well, believe it or not, there is such an “X-factor”.

_**Your beliefs**_. 

Because your beliefs are the “lens” through which you see the world. And while your “lens” might not determine reality, it _**does determine your reality.**_

So, how do we change our beliefs then?

Well, here’s what you’ve got to know first:

### 🌪️**  The Cycle of Cycles**

What we need to remember is this:

**Belief → Action → Results (→ Belief).**

To explain, imagine two people starting similar jobs:

**Person A** believes they're "not leadership material." So they don't sign up for leadership courses. When they're put in a leadership position, they fail because they’ve not practiced. Their belief that "they're not leadership material" gets stronger.

**Person B** believes leadership is _learnable_. So they take every opportunity, read books, volunteer for projects where they get exposure. When their chance comes, they succeed, reinforcing their belief that they can grow.

Same starting point. Completely different outcomes. The only difference? Their initial beliefs.

Remember: Beliefs determine actions, actions determine results, and results reinforce your belief. In this way, _**beliefs become self-fulfilling prophecies.**_

View image: (https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/319e0531-440d-467e-a64a-c9c5e49ea706/ChatGPT_Image_Jun_26__2025__04_12_08_PM__1_.png?t=1750968763)
Caption: 

And here's where it gets dangerous.

Once you have one bad experience (like _Person A_ did), your brain latches onto it as "proof" that your limiting belief was right all along. So the next time a similar opportunity comes up, you think "I failed last time, this probably won't work either."

This leads to: 

→ Taking even less action (because "what's the point?") 
→ Even worse preparation (because you're already expecting to fail) 
→ Predictably poor results (because you've set yourself up to fail) 
→ Even stronger limiting beliefs ("See? I knew I wasn't cut out for this")

It's a downward spiral that feeds on itself.

Take my friend Becca. Three years ago, she seemed super shy and had never led a team before. But here's what made the difference: she believed leadership was a skill she could improve, not some innate talent she either had or didn't have.

So when opportunities came up: 
→ She bought and read leadership books 
→ She asked her manager if she could lead more meetings 
→ She volunteered for high-priority projects when her manager was swamped

Each small win built her confidence. When her big leadership opportunity came, she was ready. She's now leading a team of almost 20 people.

The difference between Becca and someone who stays stuck isn't natural talent – it's what they believed was possible.

View image: (https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/bc5c8283-1f08-4991-b2c5-f48d72b4c0d3/image.png?t=1750960416)
Caption: 

### **🔍 Spot your career-limiting beliefs**

Most of us don't even realize we're operating under limiting beliefs. They disguise themselves as "being realistic" or "knowing your limitations."

Here are some that kill careers:

* **"I'm not good at networking"** → You avoid industry events → Your network stays small → Fewer opportunities → "See? Networking doesn't work for people like me"

* **"I could never negotiate my salary"** → You accept whatever's offered → You fall behind market rate → You feel undervalued → "I guess I'm just not worth more"

* **"I'm too old/young/inexperienced to make a career change"** → You don't even try → You stay stuck → Opportunities pass you by → "It's too late now"

The tricky part? These beliefs feel true because they've become true through your actions (or lack thereof).

**Quick exercise:** Write down one career goal you've been avoiding. Then write down why you think it won't work. That "why" is probably your limiting belief disguised as logic.

The big takeaway here is…

**Your career is shaped more by what you think is possible than by what's actually possible.**

(_write that down somewhere_)

View image: (https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/90926043-9ec3-4bd1-9136-0f023426e8cf/image.png?t=1750960398)
Caption: 

And if you're thinking "_ughh easier said than done_," do us both a favor and stop reading. I can't help you if you don't even believe change is possible.

(Ok ok I'm only joking... but also not really)

Look, if you want to break out of a negative spiral, you need to be open to the idea that you're in control of what you believe. Not completely in control - life happens - but way more in control than most people think.

----------
**…PSA: do your career a favor and **_[**follow me on LinkedIn**](https://www.linkedin.com/in/rohanmahtani/)_. 

I spend an absurd amount of time writing what I think is the _most strategic_ career advice on LinkedIn. No cringe, no fluff. Stuff that will truly benefit your career in measurable ways: strategies you can steal, email scripts you can copy/paste, AI prompts for your career, etc.

Join the 30k people who've already gotten ahead using these tactics — _[See you there](https://www.linkedin.com/comm/mynetwork/discovery-see-all?usecase=PEOPLE_FOLLOWS&followMember=rohanmahtani)_.

_alright, let’s get back to my essay…_


----------So how do you actually change these beliefs? Here are a couple of strategies that work:

### **🗃️  Curate your content diet carefully**

The easiest way to "hack" your beliefs? Change your definition of what's possible.

And the fastest way to do that? Pay attention to what stories you're consuming.

Think about it: your sense of what's "realistic" comes from the examples you see around you. If all you hear are stories about how competitive your industry is, how hard it is to break in, how AI is taking over so everyone is getting fired, how bad politics is making it harder to get jobs - _then of course you'll believe opportunities are scarce_, success is for other people, and you're lucky to have what you've got.

View image: (https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/68295212-462d-47b4-bf34-26f52492b3a8/ChatGPT_Image_Jun_26__2025__04_21_27_PM__1_.png?t=1750969321)
Caption: 

On the flipside, seek out stories of people doing exactly what you want to do - especially people who started from similar circumstances or inspirational-kinda content - and your brain starts thinking "if they can do it, maybe I can too."

And, of course, if you find yourself consuming too much ‘negativity’-fueled content, turn it back a notch: unfollow fear-mongering accounts on your socials.

(Part of the reason I write _Coached_ is to give you practical ways to improve each part of your career — a positive part of your content diet. Once you see these things *can* be improved, you'll believe it’s possible, take action, get results, which will then reinforce the belief that you can make progress.)

### 🎮**  Play a game within a game**

Let's say you just can't shake your beliefs. You can't get inspired. Then what?

Simple: Change your "actions" by playing a "game within a game."

For example:

Let's say you have the (negative) belief that "no-one would ever respond to my cold emails."

Instead of trying to win the "full game" (getting a response), you decide to narrow your focus to playing smaller games like:

* Writing hilarious cold emails that can't be ignored 

* Sending out 5 cold emails every week, regardless of how people respond

* Making it about the recipient as much as possible, not you

Because these small games are easy to act on and win… **they’ll eventually give you results in the “big game” **(a cold email response)**, which’ll change your belief.**

This works because you're building evidence through action, even when your brain is still skeptical. The small wins accumulate into proof that maybe, just maybe, your limiting belief isn't as true as you thought.

View image: (https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/27154e36-6aee-4d14-b248-3312a3ca5535/image.png?t=1750960467)
Caption: 

### 🎭**  Change how you're positioned**

One underrated way to shift beliefs? Change how you present yourself professionally.

When you beef up your LinkedIn profile, start connecting with people in your target field, and position yourself around the work you want to be doing rather than what you're currently doing - something interesting happens.

You start seeing yourself differently. And others start seeing you differently too.

It's a simple feedback loop: present yourself as someone capable of bigger things, get treated like someone capable of bigger things, start believing you're capable of bigger things.

----------
**Speaking of positioning yourself differently —**

I kept seeing friends with amazing experience get zero messages while others got flooded with opportunities. Same industry, similar backgrounds, but completely different results.

The difference? How they positioned themselves on their profiles.

We built a free LinkedIn optimization tool that shows you exactly how to reframe your experience and what to fix. Takes 30 seconds:

[Check it out here](https://resumeworded.com/linkedin-review/). 


----------### ☝ **Don’t be delusional**

Here's where people mess up the whole belief-changing thing: they set completely unrealistic expectations and then wonder why it doesn't work.

They try something once or twice, don't see instant results, and conclude "this doesn't work for me."

**It's their expectations!**

Believing that one networking event will transform your career or that reading two leadership books makes you ready to be CEO is... well, delusional.

Set realistic timelines, or you'll quit before anything actually happens.

View image: (https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/888208b4-3a8d-405d-b8e7-3a5a526e7bb4/ChatGPT_Image_Jun_26__2025__04_09_43_PM__1_.png?t=1750968604)
Caption: 

And that’s a wrap! __**Now**___, don’t skip this part._

These emails take me freakin’ forever to write up. And cost a lot in email sending costs. But yet I don’t litter them with ads nor paywall the best parts. 

All I want in return is one small favor:

**If you found this useful**, please do any of the following:

----------
#### **1. Know someone on a job search? Tell them about Resume Worded. **

It’ll make their job search a lot shorter. They can get a free resume review at [resumeworded.com/free-resume-review](https://resumeworded.com/free-resume-review)

#### **2. Got a smart friend who LOVES getting better? Tell them about Coached.**

I love seeing them reach people who want more out of their careers. If you want to share this essay with a friend, or colleague, here’s a link to it: [coached.com/essays/the-belief-factor/](https://coached.com/essays/the-belief-factor/) - I promise to keep the quality of my emails high so they love you for it.

#### **3. **[**Leave a quick review for Coached**](https://resumeworded.com/workers/newsletter-review?selected_rating=2)**.**

You get ideas that change your career for the better. In return, a short 30-second review would make me feel good about spending the time to write this. I think it’s a fair trade. [**Do it here**](https://resumeworded.com/workers/newsletter-review?selected_rating=2)**.**


----------View image: (https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/48c34338-5072-454b-b3a8-740bb45ec8ba/image.png)
Caption:
